Editor's note: This report focuses on Chongqing as part of our special series, "Rising Star Cities," about Chinese cities whose annual GDP exceeds 1 trillion yuan ($155.4 billion, or more than the GDP of Qatar). At the end of 2020, there were 23 such cities. Click here for more stories on Chongqing. You can also explore our earlier coverage of Ningbo and Changsha. Chongqing's high-rise buildings dot the winding landscape, and the city's yellow cabs add a pop of color to the scenery. Only experienced drivers are familiar with the magic of 8D transportation, and they can put on a fast and furious show anytime, anywhere. Follow CGTN into Chongqing to experience the speed of a taxi!